400.comment:
A fast-paced scrabble-like word game.  Tiles move onto one end of your tray and you have to make words before they fall off the other end.

Shared scores can be viewed using the QBFScoresViewer.

513.source:
function doShowRules(val) {
    if (!val) return;
    var rules = "QuickBrownFox lets you make words from letter tiles that move along a rack.  " +
        "The letters arrive from the right on a conveyor belt, and drop off on the left.  " +
        "Type any letter on the rack to build a word in the outbox, and then hit enter to score that word.  " +
        "Words are scored by the sum of the point values of their letters.  Scores for long words " +
        "are multiplied by a further bonus factor.  Invalid (??) or repeated (xx) words are scored " +
        "against you (but only singly), as are unused letters that fall off to the left.  " +
       "You get 100 letters to play with;  together they are worth 193 points.\n" +
       "\n" +
        "\tThe delete key or button retracts the most recent letter added.\n" +
        "\tThe esc key or 'clear' button retracts all letters from the outbox.\n" +
        "\tThe enter key or button submits the word currently in the outbox.\n" +
        "Collapse/expand of the window will pause/resume the game.\n" +
       "\n" +
        "Use the quick button to choose your speed (and thus difficulty) of play...\n" +
        "\tNot-so-quick has a longer tray and thus one more letter.\n" +
        "\tSuper-quick has a shorter conveyor so the letters come faster.\n" +
        "High scores and best words are tallied for each level of play.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "QuickBrownFox was inspired by Shuffled Word and written by Dan Ingalls.  " +
        "It was developed and deployed as a web page using the Lively Kernel development system."
    this.world().addTextWindow(
        {title: "About QuickBrownFox", 
        position: this.worldPoint(pt(-30, 100)),
        extent: pt(555,310),
        acceptInput: false,
        content: rules}
    );
	
}
